<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dug" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dug,</orth> pap, teat; used in the sing. of human mothers: <cit><quote>with mother's d. between its lips,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.393" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 393</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 3, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 3, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 195</bibl>. (In <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 7</bibl> some blundering M. Edd. <emph>dug</emph> for <emph>dung</emph> of O. Edd.). In the plur. of beasts as well as women: <bibl n="shak. ven 875" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 875</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 4, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.90" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 3, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 30</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>